snippet: Still mourning its coach, who died in January, Nazareth High of Brooklyn won the championship game of the New York State Girls’ Catholic High School Athletic Association tournament on Saturday.
abstract: Nazareth High of Brooklyn crushes Moore Catholic, 68-46, to capture the championship of the New York State Girls’ Catholic High School Athletic Association tournament.
lead_paragraph: Still mourning its coach, who died in January, Nazareth High of Brooklyn won the championship game of the New York State Girls’ Catholic High School Athletic Association tournament on Saturday.

headline.seo: A Title for Nazareth, but the Celebration Is Bittersweet
